title: High Gender Equality Rating
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan achieved a CPIA gender equality rating of 4.5, indicating a strong commitment to gender equality compared to global standards.

title: Efficient Revenue Mobilization
description: Uzbekistan scored 4.5 in the CPIA efficiency of revenue mobilization rating in 2023, reflecting effective strategies in collecting and managing public revenues.

title: High Educational Attainment
description: By 2022, 99.98% of Uzbekistan's population aged 25+ had completed at least lower secondary education, showcasing a well-educated populace.

title: Low Primary School Repetition Rates
description: In 2018, the repetition rate for primary education in Uzbekistan was 0.00125%, one of the lowest globally, indicating effective primary education systems.

title: Significant Net Borrowing
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan's net borrowing was -51,491,089,426,083.6 LCU, highlighting a substantial fiscal deficit that may impact economic stability.

title: High Compensation of Employees
description: The compensation of employees in Uzbekistan reached 60,189,419,334,713.6 LCU in 2023, reflecting significant public sector wage expenditures.

title: High Other Expenses
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan's other expenses amounted to 61,285,584,505,848.5 LCU, indicating substantial non-wage government spending.

title: Low Labor Force with Basic Education
description: As of 2020, only 12.621% of Uzbekistan's working-age population had basic education, suggesting a need for improved educational access and quality.
